# Figma Design System Rules — jakesheiner.github.io

This document captures how to translate Figma designs into this codebase. The site is a **static HTML/CSS/JS portfolio** with no framework or build step.

---

## 1. Design System Structure (Codebase Analysis)

### 1.1 Token Definitions

- **Where:** There is no separate token file. Visual tokens are **hardcoded in `styles.css`**.
- **Format:** Raw hex/rgb values in CSS. No CSS variables or theme object.
- **Transformation:** None.

**Canonical palette (use these values when matching Figma to code):**

| Role | Value | Usage in codebase |
|------|--------|-------------------|
| Brand / accent | `#ee3062` | Header name, nav hover, case-block-impact label, “That’s all folks” |
| Cream / off-white | `#FAF9F6` | Body (scrolled), button default background |
| Primary text | `#333` | Body text, headings, project titles |
| Muted text | `#949494` | .small, .hero-intro, .right column |
| White | `#fff` | Hero text and buttons on index |
| Dark UI | `#555` | Nav, button border/text, footer-style |
| Borders / frames | `#e8e8e8`, `#ddd`, `#bbb` | Case blocks, project borders |
| Problem label | `#c44` | .case-block-problem .case-block-label |
| Solution label | `#2a7` | .case-block-solution .case-block-label |
| Impact label | `#ee3062` | .case-block-impact .case-block-label |

When implementing from Figma, **map design colors to these exact hex values** so new sections stay consistent with existing pages.

### 1.2 Component Library

- **Where:** No separate component library. “Components” are **reusable HTML patterns + CSS classes** in `styles.css`.
- **Architecture:** Class-based; no JS components or partials. Each page is a full HTML file that shares `styles.css`.
- **Documentation:** None (no Storybook or component docs).

**Reusable patterns to prefer:**

- **Layout:** `.header-container`, `.row`, `.column`, `.portfolio`, `.project`, `.project-content`, `.project-text-wrapper`, `.project-text`, `.project-tags`, `.project-image`
- **Case studies:** `.details`, `.details-section`, `.case-block`, `.case-block-problem` / `.case-block-solution` / `.case-block-impact`, `.case-block-label`, `.comparison-levels-row`, `.comparison-level-item`, `.comparison-level-frame`, `.details-graphs`, `.graph-item`, `.graph-item-copy`
- **Buttons:** `.button-24` (pill style, used site-wide)
- **Typography:** `.bigger`, `.small`, `.hero-intro`
- **Gallup-specific:** `.details.gallup-case-study`, `.gallup-case-study-title`

When Figma shows a card, case block, or CTA, **reuse these class names and structure** instead of inventing new ones.

### 1.3 Frameworks & Libraries

- **UI:** None. Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
- **Styling:** Single global stylesheet `styles.css`. No Tailwind, CSS Modules, or styled-components.
- **Build:** No bundler. Static files only (e.g. GitHub Pages).

**Implication for Figma MCP:** Treat MCP output (e.g. React + Tailwind) as **design and layout reference only**. Implement in **plain HTML + existing classes in `styles.css`** (or new classes that follow the same patterns).

### 1.4 Asset Management

- **Storage:**  
  - Images: `images/` (e.g. `images/favicon.svg`, `images/muse_hero.JPG`).  
  - Video: `videos/` (e.g. `videos/gallup.mov`).
- **Reference:** Relative paths in HTML/CSS, e.g. `src="images/…"`, `href="images/…"`.
- **Optimization:** None automated. Images are used as-is (PNG, JPG, SVG).
- **CDN:** Only for third-party: Google Fonts, Bootstrap Icons (see Icons).

**Rule:** New assets from Figma (exports, screenshots) should be placed in `images/` (or `videos/` for video) and referenced with relative paths from the HTML file (e.g. `images/` for pages in repo root).

### 1.5 Icon System

- **Source:** Bootstrap Icons, loaded via CDN in `<head>`:
  - `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css`
- **Usage:** `<i class="bi bi-<name>"></i>` (e.g. `bi bi-arrow-right`).
- **Naming:** Bootstrap Icons naming: `bi bi-<icon-name>`.

**Rule:** Do not add new icon libraries. Use Bootstrap Icons only; if Figma uses a different icon, pick the closest Bootstrap Icon or use an SVG in `images/`.

### 1.6 Styling Approach

- **Methodology:** Global CSS in one file, `styles.css`, with logical comment sections (reset, layout, case study, Gallup overrides, homepage, shared components, responsive).
- **Global styles:** Yes. Reset and base in `styles.css`; all pages share it via `<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">`.
- **Responsive:**  
  - `@media (max-width: 768px)` for mobile (stack columns, full-width main, single-column project content, etc.).  
  - `@media (min-width: 800px)` for hero layout on index.  
  - Use the same breakpoints and patterns (e.g. `.row` → column on small screens) for new layout from Figma.

**Rule:** Implement new UI with **classes in `styles.css`** (or minimal inline style only where necessary). Prefer extending existing classes (e.g. new modifiers) over one-off inline styles.

### 1.7 Project Structure

- **Root:** HTML pages at repo root: `index.html`, `gallup.html`, `muse.html`, `myQuilt.html`, `playground.html`, `vennDiagrams.html`, `ai-logo.html`, `slime.html`, `diagrams.html`, etc.
- **Shared:** `styles.css`, `castleScript.js` (and other script files where used).
- **Assets:** `images/`, `videos/`.
- **Pattern:** Each “feature” is typically one HTML page; shared header/footer and nav are repeated in each file. No templates or partials.

**Rule:** New pages from Figma should be new HTML files at root (or in a subfolder if you introduce one), each linking to `styles.css` and reusing the same `<header>` / nav pattern as existing pages.

